Remarks. Adults of
Microphorella praecox
are known to occur on sandy river banks from April to June in Central Europe ( Chvála 1983 , 1988 ;
Shamshev & Grootaert 2004
). The Swiss material from
1999 and 2000
listed above was collected (along with specimens of
M. similis
) by sweeping above gravel in the floodplain of the Rhône River in May.
